race.comment: FEARLESS PARKER (3) was in winning form two back (21.75) at this track but ran below best last time at Mandurah, finishing 7th. Form here at the trip sound including two wins. Key runner on his best form. THANK YOU JOE (1) has been out of the placings the last couple but was a Grade 5 winner (22.02) three back at this track. Can find the frame this time. ASTON FLORIN (5) missed the frame latest when eighth at Mandurah (23.73) but scored five back at Mandurah (22.41). Has a good winning strike rate at this journey. Worth another chance. CYCLONIC CLINTON (2) is worth including.
